column5: Here are some more pics from my 2008 year and some from earlier. Unfortunately I have not caught much for 2009, that will hopefully change soon when I get out again. Anyways, some pics of fish.  Trout               City pike      I will post bass and musky another time.
Some real beasts you got there!  Good Job

I like the pictures with the CN tower in the background.  It's cool to think that even in one of Canada's largest cities, you still have a decent chance of putting a good bend in your rod.   Those are some nice fish, Dude.
WOW it's even better in part 2.... again congratulations  Is that a brown in the second pic?  Amazing colors on that fish Thanks for sharing Leechman

great bunch of photo's . 3 really stand out to me .  1\ the colours on that football shaped brown  2\ rainbow in the shot with the wall of ice surrounding you  3\ the girth on the city pike , what a gut. all great fish for sure.  thanks for sharin'
That second fish is beautiful! All the others are great also!
cool pics, love the steelie shot with all the ice and winter backdrop
Thanks for the kind words guys. Hey MSP, maybe soon you'll have a spot named after you in that lake.
